description._content: Catalog #: 09_01615 Title: First Lieutenant Harry Haw Special Collection Photo Desmet South Dakota Additional Information: Harry Haw (on left) with Kelby and a JN-4D ""Jenny"" aircraft in Desmet South Dakota 1920. Handwritten inscription ""Passenger & Pilot - Old 5113 June 11, 1920"", Harry Haw served in the U.S. Army in the 514th Observation Squadron. He entered the U.S. Army in 1917 and became a First Lieutenant in 1930. He became a civilian Transport Pilot by 1930 and had logged 789 flying hours by 1934. he later became Principal of the Alice Birney school.
